<H1>Russ Miller, Professor</H1>

<!WA0><A HREF="http://www.cs.buffalo.edu/pub/WWW/faculty/miller/miller_color.jpeg"><!WA1><IMG SRC="http://www.cs.buffalo.edu/pub/WWW/faculty/miller/miller_color.gif" ALT=""></A> <P>

<!IMG SRC="Bars/BLUE_LINE.gif">
<!IMG SRC="Bars/BlueMarbleLine.gif">
<!IMG SRC="Bars/bluefade.gif">
<!IMG SRC="Bars/gradiated-6pt.grey-line.gif">


<!WA2><IMG SRC="http://www.cs.buffalo.edu/pub/WWW/faculty/miller/Bars/miller.gif">
<P>
Russ Miller is
<UL>
<LI>
<strong>Professor</strong> of
<!WA3><A HREF="http://www.cs.buffalo.edu/"><strong>Computer Science</strong></A>
at <!WA4><A HREF="http://www.cs.buffalo.edu/pub/WWW/ub.html"><strong>SUNY-Buffalo</str
ong></A>
<LI>
<strong>Senior Research Scientist</strong> at the
<!WA5><A HREF="http://www.hwi.buffalo.edu/"><strong>Hauptman-Woodward
Medical Research Institute</strong></A>
<LI>
<strong>Managing partner</strong> of
<!WA6><A HREF="http://www.crs-web.com/"><strong>CRS Web Solutions</strong></A>
</UL>
He received a B.S, M.A., and Ph.D. from the <!WA7><A
HREF="http://www.math.binghamton.edu/"><strong>Department of Mathematical Sciences,</strong></A>
<!WA8><A HREF="http://www.binghamton.edu/"><strong>SUNY-Binghamton</strong></A>,
in 1980, 1982, and 1985, respectively.


<P>
Professor Miller's research interests include 
<!WA9><A HREF="http://www.cs.buffalo.edu/pub/WWW/research.html#prog11"><strong>parallel algorithms</strong></A>, 
image processing,
<!WA10><A HREF="http://www.cs.buffalo.edu/pub/WWW/faculty/miller/crystal.html"><strong>computational crystallography</strong></A>, 
and <!WA11><A HREF="http://www.cs.rit.edu/~ncs/parallel.html"><strong>parallel processing
education</strong></A>.  
Dr. Miller is on the editorial board of <I>Parallel Processing
Letters</I>, has served on the program committee for a variety of conferences
involving parallelism and image processing, and is on the executive
committee of the 
<!WA12><A HREF="http://www.computer.org/tab/tab.htm#tabpp"><strong>IEEE
Technical Committee on Parallel Processing</strong></A>.</BR>

</BR>
